outputs.description: 3.1.1 By 2017, the program will contribute with integration initiatives and programmatic coordination to raise awareness aboutpopulations that have been excluded and promote changes in behavior and knowledge.
1.2.2 By 2017 the National Integrated Child Protection System (SNPI) has an established mechanism to monitor and evaluate itsperformance and results.

1.2.1 By 2017, 20 cantons with the lowest welfare indicators have improved protection services against the different forms ofviolence for children and adolescents, in the family, the community and the school.
By 2012, child-rearing practices that are respect children's rights are promoted amongst parents and caregivers in order to bringabout behaviour and culture change.
Effective and efficient governance and systems to manage risks and achieve programme results.
Effective and efficient management of Human capacity including staff development and learning and staff well-being.
Effective and efficient management and stewardship of financial resources related to office administration.

1.1.1 By 2017, an enhanced education system resulted in an increased number of children and adolescents living in regions with thegreatest social/education inequities that complete primary and secondary within the standard timeframes.

1.1.2 By 2017 in regions of greatest social exclusion, a targeted integrated early childhood development policy is applied,implemented by the relevant government agencies granting access to child care services for the most vulnerable children ages 0-7
2.1.2 By 2017, Costa Rican social sectors and civil society organizations have increased capacity to monitor equity-based resultsand undertake evidence-based advocacy.

2.1.1 By 2017, the Children and Adolescents' Information System (SINA) generates information that informs policy makers  for theformulation and revisions of legislations, public policies and programs targeted at reducing inequities .
